CONTAGIOUS BOVINE PLEUROPNEUMONIA - NAMIBIA: (KAVANGO WEST) OIE
***************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 26 Jun 2019
Source: OIE, WAHID [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=30891


Contagious bovine pleuropneumonia [CBPP], Namibia
-----------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 26 Jun 2019 from Dr. Adrianatus Florentius Maseke, Chief Veterinary Officer, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Water and Forestry, Windhoek, Namibia

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 20 May 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 27 May 2019
Report date: 26 Jun 2019
Date submitted to OIE: 26 Jun 2019
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 12 Feb 2019
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Mycoplasma mycoides_
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (3)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 3
Outbreak location: Kavango West
Date of start of the outbreak: 20 May 2019
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / - / 3 / 3 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Three adult cattle died with a history of coughing.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Illegal movement of animals

Control measures
Measures applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s) [Kavango West, 1133 cattle vaccinated]; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; traceability; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Central veterinary laboratory (National laboratory)
Tests and results
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 27 May 2019 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In August 2018, Namibia reported 3 outbreaks of CBPP. The locations of these outbreaks were Kavango West (where the current outbreak is located) and Kavango East. The event was resolved in February 2019. See event summary and map at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=27753. - Mod.CRD

HealthMap/ProMED map available at:
Kavango, Namibia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6539922,1380]
